import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Extract data from the loaded file
accuracy_data = nb_lemm_data['Accuracy_ros_nb_lemmatized']
precision_data = nb_lemm_data['Precision_ros_nb_lemmatized']
recall_data = nb_lemm_data['Recall_ros_nb_lemmatized']
f1_score_data = nb_lemm_data['F1 Score_ros_nb_lemmatized']

# Create a figure
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

# Bar chart with different colors for each metric
bar_width = 0.2
space_between_bars = 0.2
index = np.arange(1)  # For a single category

bar1 = ax.bar(index - 1.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [accuracy_data], bar_width, label='Accuracy', color='blue')
bar2 = ax.bar(index - 0.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [precision_data], bar_width, label='Precision', color='green')
bar3 = ax.bar(index + 0.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [recall_data], bar_width, label='Recall', color='orange')
bar4 = ax.bar(index + 1.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [f1_score_data], bar_width, label='F1 Score', color='red')

# Add labels, title, and legend
ax.set_xlabel('Metrics')
ax.set_ylabel('Score')
ax.set_title('Metrics for NB - Lemmatized')
ax.set_xticks(index)
ax.set_xticklabels(['Class'])
ax.legend()

# Add data callouts (annotations)
def add_data_callout(bars, data, offset=0):
    for bar, value in zip(bars, data):
        ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2 + offset, bar.get_height(),
                f'{value:.2f}', ha='center', va='bottom')

add_data_callout(bar1, [accuracy_data], offset=0.03)
add_data_callout(bar2, [precision_data], offset=0.03)
add_data_callout(bar3, [recall_data], offset=0.03)
add_data_callout(bar4, [f1_score_data], offset=0.03)

# Save the figure to a PDF file
pdf_filename = "metrics_nb_lemmatized.pdf"
plt.savefig(pdf_filename)
print(f"Metrics saved to {pdf_filename}")

# Show the plot (optional)
plt.show()

In [160]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.metrics import auc, roc_curve

# Load necessary data
fpr_data_dict = nb_lemm_data['FPR_ros_nb_lemmatized'][()]
tpr_data_dict = nb_lemm_data['TPR_ros_nb_lemmatized'][()]
roc_auc_data_dict = nb_lemm_data['ROC AUC_ros_nb_lemmatized'][()]

# Convert NumPy arrays to lists
fpr_data = {class_label: np.array(fpr_data_dict[class_label]) for class_label in fpr_data_dict}
tpr_data = {class_label: np.array(tpr_data_dict[class_label]) for class_label in tpr_data_dict}
roc_auc_data = {class_label: np.float64(roc_auc_data_dict[class_label]) for class_label in roc_auc_data_dict}

# Ensure all arrays have the same length using interpolation
max_length = max(len(arr) for arr in fpr_data.values())
for class_label in fpr_data:
    fpr_data[class_label] = np.interp(np.linspace(0, 1, max_length), np.linspace(0, 1, len(fpr_data[class_label])), fpr_data[class_label])
    tpr_data[class_label] = np.interp(np.linspace(0, 1, max_length), np.linspace(0, 1, len(tpr_data[class_label])), tpr_data[class_label])

# Calculate macro-average FPR and TPR
macro_fpr = np.mean([fpr_data[class_label] for class_label in fpr_data], axis=0)
macro_tpr = np.mean([tpr_data[class_label] for class_label in tpr_data], axis=0)

# Calculate macro-average AUC
macro_auc = auc(macro_fpr, macro_tpr)

# Plot ROC curve for macro-average
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(macro_fpr, macro_tpr, label=f'Macro-average (AUC = {macro_auc:.2f})', color='navy')

plt.title('Macro-average ROC Curve (Naive Bayes - Lemmatized)')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Specify the file path for SVM metrics
metrics_file_path_svm = "svm_metrics_df_lemm.csv"

# Import the CSV file into a DataFrame
svm_metrics_df = pd.read_csv(metrics_file_path_svm)

# Extract data from the DataFrame
accuracy_data_svm = svm_metrics_df.loc[svm_metrics_df['Metric'] == 'Accuracy', 'Value'].values[0]
precision_data_svm = svm_metrics_df.loc[svm_metrics_df['Metric'] == 'Precision', 'Value'].values[0]
recall_data_svm = svm_metrics_df.loc[svm_metrics_df['Metric'] == 'Recall', 'Value'].values[0]
f1_score_data_svm = svm_metrics_df.loc[svm_metrics_df['Metric'] == 'F1 Score', 'Value'].values[0]

# Create a figure
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

# Bar chart with different colors for each metric
bar_width = 0.2
space_between_bars = 0.2
index = np.arange(1)  # For a single category

bar1_svm = ax.bar(index - 1.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [accuracy_data_svm], bar_width, label='Accuracy', color='blue')
bar2_svm = ax.bar(index - 0.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [precision_data_svm], bar_width, label='Precision', color='green')
bar3_svm = ax.bar(index + 0.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [recall_data_svm], bar_width, label='Recall', color='orange')
bar4_svm = ax.bar(index + 1.5 * (bar_width + space_between_bars), [f1_score_data_svm], bar_width, label='F1 Score', color='red')

# Add labels, title, and legend
ax.set_xlabel('Metrics')
ax.set_ylabel('Score')
ax.set_title('Metrics for SVM - Lemmatized')
ax.set_xticks(index)
ax.set_xticklabels(['Class'])
ax.legend()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import auc, roc_curve

# Load necessary data for SVM
fpr_data_dict_svm = svm_lemm_data['FPR_ros_svm_lemmatized'][()]
tpr_data_dict_svm = svm_lemm_data['TPR_ros_svm_lemmatized'][()]
roc_auc_data_dict_svm = svm_lemm_data['ROC AUC_ros_svm_lemmatized'][()]

# Convert NumPy arrays to lists for SVM
fpr_data_svm = {class_label: np.array(fpr_data_dict_svm[class_label]) for class_label in fpr_data_dict_svm}
tpr_data_svm = {class_label: np.array(tpr_data_dict_svm[class_label]) for class_label in tpr_data_dict_svm}
roc_auc_data_svm = {class_label: np.float64(roc_auc_data_dict_svm[class_label]) for class_label in roc_auc_data_dict_svm}

# Ensure all arrays have the same length using interpolation for SVM
max_length_svm = max(len(arr) for arr in fpr_data_svm.values())
for class_label in fpr_data_svm:
    fpr_data_svm[class_label] = np.interp(np.linspace(0, 1, max_length_svm), np.linspace(0, 1, len(fpr_data_svm[class_label])), fpr_data_svm[class_label])
    tpr_data_svm[class_label] = np.interp(np.linspace(0, 1, max_length_svm), np.linspace(0, 1, len(tpr_data_svm[class_label])), tpr_data_svm[class_label])

# Calculate macro-average FPR and TPR for SVM
macro_fpr_svm = np.mean([fpr_data_svm[class_label] for class_label in fpr_data_svm], axis=0)
macro_tpr_svm = np.mean([tpr_data_svm[class_label] for class_label in tpr_data_svm], axis=0)

# Calculate macro-average AUC for SVM
macro_auc_svm = auc(macro_fpr_svm, macro_tpr_svm)

# Plot ROC curve for macro-average for SVM
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(macro_fpr_svm, macro_tpr_svm, label=f'Macro-average (AUC = {macro_auc_svm:.2f})', color='darkorange')

plt.title('Macro-average ROC Curve (SVM - Lemmatized)')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.preprocessing import label_binarize

# Load predictions and true labels from the saved file
loaded_data = np.load('roc_auc_bert_oversampled.npz')
loaded_predictions = loaded_data['predictions']
loaded_true_labels = loaded_data['true_labels']

# Binarize the true labels for multi-class ROC-AUC
num_classes = len(np.unique(loaded_true_labels))
binarized_true_labels = label_binarize(loaded_true_labels, classes=np.arange(num_classes))

# Calculate ROC curve and AUC for each class (one-vs-rest)
fpr = dict()
tpr = dict()
roc_auc = dict()

for i in range(num_classes):
    fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(binarized_true_labels[:, i], loaded_predictions == i)
    roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])

# Calculate mean FPR and mean TPR
mean_fpr = np.mean([fpr[i] for i in range(num_classes)], axis=0)
mean_tpr = np.mean([tpr[i] for i in range(num_classes)], axis=0)

# Calculate macro-average ROC-AUC
roc_auc_macro = auc(mean_fpr, mean_tpr)

# Plot macro-average ROC-AUC
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(mean_fpr, mean_tpr, color='darkorange', lw=2, label=f'Macro Avg. AUC = {roc_auc_macro:.2f}')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='navy', lw=2, linestyle='--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.title('ROC-AUC Curve for Multi-Class Classification')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import auc, roc_curve

# Load necessary data for non-lemmatized NB
fpr_data_dict_not_lemm = nb_not_lemm_data['FPR_ros_nb_not_lemmatized'][()]
tpr_data_dict_not_lemm = nb_not_lemm_data['TPR_ros_nb_not_lemmatized'][()]
roc_auc_data_dict_not_lemm = nb_not_lemm_data['ROC AUC_ros_nb_not_lemmatized'][()]

# Convert NumPy arrays to lists for non-lemmatized NB
fpr_data_not_lemm = {class_label: np.array(fpr_data_dict_not_lemm[class_label]) for class_label in fpr_data_dict_not_lemm}
tpr_data_not_lemm = {class_label: np.array(tpr_data_dict_not_lemm[class_label]) for class_label in tpr_data_dict_not_lemm}
roc_auc_data_not_lemm = {class_label: np.float64(roc_auc_data_dict_not_lemm[class_label]) for class_label in roc_auc_data_dict_not_lemm}

# Ensure all arrays have the same length using interpolation for non-lemmatized NB
max_length_not_lemm = max(len(arr) for arr in fpr_data_not_lemm.values())
for class_label in fpr_data_not_lemm:
    fpr_data_not_lemm[class_label] = np.interp(
        np.linspace(0, 1, max_length_not_lemm),
        np.linspace(0, 1, len(fpr_data_not_lemm[class_label])),
        fpr_data_not_lemm[class_label]
    )
    tpr_data_not_lemm[class_label] = np.interp(
        np.linspace(0, 1, max_length_not_lemm),
        np.linspace(0, 1, len(tpr_data_not_lemm[class_label])),
        tpr_data_not_lemm[class_label]
    )

# Calculate macro-average FPR and TPR for non-lemmatized NB
macro_fpr_not_lemm = np.mean([fpr_data_not_lemm[class_label] for class_label in fpr_data_not_lemm], axis=0)
macro_tpr_not_lemm = np.mean([tpr_data_not_lemm[class_label] for class_label in tpr_data_not_lemm], axis=0)

# Calculate macro-average AUC for non-lemmatized NB
macro_auc_not_lemm = auc(macro_fpr_not_lemm, macro_tpr_not_lemm)

# Plot ROC curve for macro-average for non-lemmatized NB
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(macro_fpr_not_lemm, macro_tpr_not_lemm, label=f'NB (Non-Lemmatized) - Macro-average (AUC = {macro_auc_not_lemm:.2f})', color='orange')

plt.title('Macro-average ROC Curve (Naive Bayes - Non-Lemmatized)')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import auc

# Assuming you have loaded FPR, TPR, and ROC AUC for non-lemmatized FastText with CNN
# using the loaded_fpr_cnn_n_lemm, loaded_tpr_cnn_n_lemm, loaded_roc_auc_cnn_n_lemm variables

# Convert NumPy arrays to lists for non-lemmatized FastText with CNN
fpr_data_cnn_n_lemm = [loaded_fpr_cnn_n_lemm[key] for key in loaded_fpr_cnn_n_lemm]
tpr_data_cnn_n_lemm = [loaded_tpr_cnn_n_lemm[key] for key in loaded_tpr_cnn_n_lemm]

# Ensure all arrays have the same length using interpolation
max_length_cnn_n_lemm = max(len(arr) for arr in fpr_data_cnn_n_lemm + tpr_data_cnn_n_lemm)
fpr_data_cnn_n_lemm = [np.interp(np.linspace(0, 1, max_length_cnn_n_lemm), np.linspace(0, 1, len(arr)), arr) for arr in fpr_data_cnn_n_lemm]
tpr_data_cnn_n_lemm = [np.interp(np.linspace(0, 1, max_length_cnn_n_lemm), np.linspace(0, 1, len(arr)), arr) for arr in tpr_data_cnn_n_lemm]

# Calculate macro-average FPR and TPR for non-lemmatized FastText with CNN
macro_fpr_cnn_n_lemm = np.mean(fpr_data_cnn_n_lemm, axis=0)
macro_tpr_cnn_n_lemm = np.mean(tpr_data_cnn_n_lemm, axis=0)

# Plot macro-average ROC curve for non-lemmatized FastText with CNN

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.preprocessing import label_binarize

# Load predictions and true labels from the saved file
loaded_data = np.load('roc_auc_bert__ros_n_lemm.npz')
loaded_predictionsn_lemm = loaded_data['predictions']
loaded_true_labelsn_lemm = loaded_data['true_labels']

# Binarize the true labels for multi-class ROC-AUC
num_classes = len(np.unique(loaded_true_labelsn_lemm))
binarized_true_labels = label_binarize(loaded_true_labelsn_lemm, classes=np.arange(num_classes))

# Calculate ROC curve and AUC for each class (one-vs-rest)
fprn_lemm = dict()
tprn_lemm = dict()
roc_aucn_lemm = dict()

for i in range(num_classes):
    fprn_lemm[i], tprn_lemm[i], _ = roc_curve(binarized_true_labels[:, i], loaded_predictionsn_lemm == i)
    roc_aucn_lemm[i] = auc(fprn_lemm[i], tprn_lemm[i])

# Calculate mean FPR and mean TPR
mean_fprn_lemm = np.mean([fprn_lemm[i] for i in range(num_classes)], axis=0)
mean_tprn_lemm = np.mean([tprn_lemm[i] for i in range(num_classes)], axis=0)

# Calculate macro-average ROC-AUC
roc_auc_macron_lemm = auc(mean_fprn_lemm, mean_tprn_lemm)

# Plot macro-average ROC-AUC
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(mean_fprn_lemm, mean_tprn_lemm, color='darkorange', lw=2, label=f'Macro Avg. AUC = {roc_auc_macron_lemm:.2f}')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='navy', lw=2, linestyle='--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.title('ROC-AUC Curve for Multi-Class Classification')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()

from matplotlib.cm import viridis

# Load necessary data for lemmatized and non-lemmatized models

    ("FastText with SVM (Lemmatized)", macro_fpr_ft_svm, macro_tpr_ft_svm, macro_auc_ft_svm),
    ("FastText with CNN (Lemmatized)", all_fpr_loaded, mean_tpr_loaded, roc_auc_macro_loaded),
    ("BERT (Lemmatized)", mean_fpr, mean_tpr, roc_auc_macro)

# Define models and corresponding data for non-lemmatized models

    ("SVM (Non-Lemmatized)", macro_fpr_svm_not_lemm, macro_tpr_svm_not_lemm, macro_auc_svm_not_lemm),

]

    axes[0].plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{model_name} (AUC = {auc_value:.2f})', color=color)

# Add labels, legends, and title for the lemmatized ROC curves

# Add label directly beneath the lemmatized chart
axes[0].text(0.5, -0.15, 'a) Lemmatized', ha='center', va='center', fontsize=12)

# Plot ROC curves for non-lemmatized models
for i, (model_name, fpr, tpr, auc_value) in enumerate(models_not_lemmatized):
    color = viridis(i / (len(models_not_lemmatized) - 1))  # Use Viridis color palette
    axes[1].plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{model_name} (AUC = {auc_value:.2f})', color=color)
